# Summary Module — Mobile Developer Documentation

> **Audience:** Android (Java/Kotlin) developer building a mobile app that mirrors the web summary module behavior.
> **Purpose:** Complete reference for screens, role-based UI conditions, DB rules, status flow, and API contract so the mobile UI behaves identically to the web app.

---

## 1. Domain Glossary

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| **Summary** | An inter-departmental document drafted by a department, signed by its secretary, and forwarded to other department secretaries for review/action. |
| **Section Draft** | A summary drafted by a junior officer (DEO / Section Officer) on behalf of the secretary. Goes to the secretary for review/sign before being forwarded externally. |
| **External Summary** | A summary that has been signed and forwarded out of the originating department (or was created directly by a secretary). |
| **Internal Forward / Share** | Within a department, the secretary can share an incoming summary with department members for their feedback. Each member can submit remarks back or forward to another member (chain forwarding). |
| **Remarks Added (Drafted Remarks)** | A junior officer in a non-originating department drafts a rich response (with attachments/links) on behalf of their secretary. Treated like an internal section-draft cycle. |
| **Returned to Section** | Secretary sends a draft (or drafted remarks) back to the originator/submitter for amendments. |
| **Movement** | A row in `summary_movements` representing a single action (sent, signed, returned, remarks added, etc.). Used to render the printed summary document. |
| **Local Correspondence** | Internal Daak letters or internal e-Files linked to the summary. Visible only to users in the linking department. **Never** travels to other departments. |
| **Flag Attachment** | A supporting file uploaded under a categorical "flag" label (e.g. Flag A, Flag B). |

