## 2. User Roles

The system uses `users.role_id`:

| role_id | Role | Capabilities |
|---------|------|--------------|
| **1** | Admin | Full access; treated as secretary in the secretary checks. |
| **2** | DEO / Section Officer | Can create section drafts; can receive internal forwards and submit remarks. |
| **3** | (other clerical) | Same as DEO for summary purposes. |
| **4** | Acting Secretary (Admin sub-role) | Treated as a secretary candidate. |
| **5** | Secretary | Owner of a department's summary inbox; can sign, forward, return, share. |

**Acting-secretary detection:** A user is *also* treated as a secretary if their **designation title** contains the string `additional secretary` or `special secretary` (case-insensitive). See `isSecretaryOrActing()` in [SummaryController.php](app/Http/Controllers/SummaryController.php#L40).

```php
// Pseudocode for "is this user a secretary in this department?"
isSecretary(user, deptId) =
    user.role_id IN (1, 5) OR
    designation_title CONTAINS "additional secretary" OR
    designation_title CONTAINS "special secretary"
    AND
    user belongs to deptId
```

The mobile app should fetch and store the role_id and designation title for the logged-in user at login.

