## 3. Permissions (server-side `can()` checks)

| Permission Slug | Used By | Mobile Action Restriction |
|-----------------|---------|---------------------------|
| `summary_create` | Create summary, create draft, store, store-draft | Hide "Create Draft" / "New Summary" buttons if missing |
| `summary_secretary_inbox` | Index page access for secretary | Hide secretary tabs if missing |
| `summary_internal_view` | View summaries assigned via internal forward | Hide pending action tab if missing |
| `summary_internal_remarks` | Submit remarks via internal-action page | Hide remarks submission UI if missing |

**Module gate:** Any of the four above permissions allows access to the module (`canAccessSummaryModule`). Always check before showing the summary navigation entry.

