## 4. Database Schema (relevant tables)

### 4.1 `summaries`
| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| id | bigint | PK |
| summary_no | string(50) | Unique. Format `SUM/{ABBR}/{YEAR}/{6-digit-seq}` |
| subject | text | |
| summary_date | date | |
| body | longtext | The main summary content (HTML from rich editor) |
| originating_department_id | FK departments | Department that created the summary |
| current_department_id | FK departments | Where the summary currently lives |
| originating_user_desg_id | FK user_desgs | User who originally created it (DEO or Secretary) |
| current_holder_user_desg_id | FK user_desgs | Who currently has it on their desk |
| current_status | tinyint | See **Status Codes** below |
| summary_type | enum | `external` (default) or `section_draft` |
| draft_target_department_id | FK departments (nullable) | For section drafts: target dept the secretary will forward to |
| created_at, updated_at | timestamps | |

#### Status Codes (`current_status`)
| Code | Constant | Label | Badge |
|------|----------|-------|-------|
| 1 | STATUS_PENDING_SECRETARY | Pending with Secretary | warning (yellow) |
| 2 | STATUS_SHARED_INTERNALLY | Shared Internally for Feedback | info (cyan) |
| 3 | STATUS_COLLECTING_REMARKS | Collecting Internal Remarks | primary (blue) |
| 4 | STATUS_READY_TO_FORWARD | Ready to Forward | success (green) |
| 5 | STATUS_FORWARDED_NEXT_DEPARTMENT | Forwarded to Next Department | secondary (grey) |
| 6 | STATUS_CLOSED | Closed / Final | dark |
| 7 | STATUS_SECTION_DRAFT | Draft from Section | danger (red/orange) |

### 4.2 `summary_attachments`
| Column | Notes |
|--------|-------|
| id, summary_id, uploaded_by_user_desg_id | |
| attachment_type | enum: `supporting` |
| original_name | If a flag is set, prefixed `[Flag: <FlagTitle>] filename.pdf`. The first attachment per summary is treated as the **main PDF** (no flag prefix). |
| stored_name, file_path, mime_type, file_size | |

**The first attachment is always the Main Summary PDF.** All others are flag attachments.

### 4.3 `summary_movements`
| Column | Notes |
|--------|-------|
| id, summary_id | |
| from_department_id, to_department_id | |
| from_user_desg_id, to_user_desg_id | |
| acted_by_user_desg_id | The actual logged-in user that performed the action |
| action_type | enum: `created`, `sent_to_department`, `shared_internally`, `remarks_added`, `signed_and_forwarded`, `closed`, `returned_to_section` |
| remarks | Text (HTML) — content shown on the summary document for that movement |
| secretary_signature_path | NULL when unsigned (draft remarks). Set to a `storage/...png` path when signed. |
| acted_at | datetime |

**Action type meaning:**

| action_type | Created when | from_dept == to_dept ? |
|-------------|--------------|------------------------|
| `created` | Reserved (not currently used) | |
| `sent_to_department` | (a) Secretary creates summary and sends to target dept, OR (b) DEO submits a section draft to own secretary | (b) **same dept** |
| `shared_internally` | Secretary shares with internal users (not currently used as a movement; uses `summary_internal_forwards`) | |
| `remarks_added` | A user inside a department drafts rich remarks (via internal-action page). Stays unsigned until the secretary signs. | **same dept** |
| `signed_and_forwarded` | Secretary signs and forwards externally. **If an unsigned `remarks_added` from this dept exists, it is updated in place (action_type changed) instead of creating a new row** — so the document shows ONE row with the drafted content + signature. | **different dept** |
| `returned_to_section` | Secretary returns a draft/remarks to the originator/submitter | **same dept** |
| `closed` | Reserved | |

### 4.4 `summary_internal_forwards`
| Column | Notes |
|--------|-------|
| id, summary_id | |
| forwarded_by_user_desg_id | Who shared/forwarded |
| forwarded_to_user_desg_id | Who received |
| instruction | Optional text from the sender |
| submitted_remarks | Set when the recipient submits remarks back (status 2) |
| status | tinyint: `1=Pending`, `2=Remarks Submitted`, `3=Closed` |
| submitted_at | datetime when status changed to 2 |

### 4.5 `summary_remarks`
| Column | Notes |
|--------|-------|
| id, summary_id, internal_forward_id | |
| submitted_by_user_desg_id | |
| remark_type | enum: `forwarding` (a single forwarding remark) or `para` (a numbered paragraph) |
| para_number | Sequential when remark_type=para |
| heading | Optional heading for a para |
| content | Rich HTML |

### 4.6 `summary_local_links`
| Column | Notes |
|--------|-------|
| id, summary_id | |
| link_type | `daak` or `file` |
| daak_letter_id (nullable) | When type=daak |
| file_id (nullable) | When type=file |
| linked_by_user_desg_id | Used to filter visibility — only users in the same department as the linker see this link |

### 4.7 `summary_internal_files`
| Column | Notes |
|--------|-------|
| id, summary_id, internal_forward_id, file_id, created_by_user_desg_id | Links a generated internal e-file to a particular internal forward |

