## 7. Detail Screen — `GET /summaries/{id}` (Show)

This is the most complex screen. Below are **all** the variables that the controller computes and the UI conditions that depend on them.

### 7.1 Controller-computed flags (passed to view)

| Variable | Definition |
|----------|------------|
| `$isSectionDraft` | `summary.summary_type == 'section_draft'` |
| `$isInCurrentDepartment` | `summary.current_department_id == myDeptId` |
| `$isCurrentHolder` | `isInCurrentDepartment AND current_holder == me` |
| `$isCurrentSecretaryHolder` | `isCurrentHolder AND isSecretary(me, myDeptId)` |
| `$isOriginatingDepartment` | `summary.originating_department_id == myDeptId` |
| `$isDraftReturnedToMe` | `isCurrentHolder AND NOT isCurrentSecretaryHolder AND there exists a returned_to_section movement with to_user_desg_id == me` |
| `$myInternalForward` | The `summary_internal_forwards` row where `forwarded_to == me AND status == 1` (pending) |
| `$myAnyInternalForward` | Same but any status |
| `$visibleInternalForwards` | All internal forwards where `forwardedBy.dept == myDeptId OR forwardedTo.dept == myDeptId` |
| `$visibleInternalFiles` | Internal files attached to one of `$visibleInternalForwards` |
| `$localLinks` | Local links where `linked_by_user_desg_id` belongs to a user in **my** department |
| `$canSeeLocalLinks` | Always true (kept for legacy) |
| `$canPrintRemarks` | `current_status == READY_TO_FORWARD AND any visible internal forward has status=2` |
| `$hasUnsignedDeptRemarks` | There exists a `remarks_added` movement with `from_dept == myDeptId AND secretary_signature_path IS NULL` |
| `$showDraftActions` | `(isSectionDraft AND isOriginatingDepartment AND isCurrentSecretaryHolder) OR (isCurrentSecretaryHolder AND hasUnsignedDeptRemarks)` |

### 7.2 Access guard (403 abort)

The user must satisfy at least one of:
```
isInCurrentDepartment
OR isOriginatingDepartment
OR myAnyInternalForward != null
OR hasEverActed (any movement with acted_by == me)
OR wasEverInMyDept (any movement where from_dept == myDeptId OR to_dept == myDeptId)
```

### 7.3 Sections of the Detail screen

#### A. Header bar
- Back button → go to index
- Print Summary button (always visible)

#### B. Summary Document Sheet (left, ~9 cols)
The "printed" representation of the summary, built from movement rows.

##### Movement row builder algorithm
```
allMovements = summary.movements ORDER BY acted_at ASC
firstSent   = first movement with action_type='sent_to_department'
wasSectionDraft = isSectionDraft OR (firstSent.from_dept == firstSent.to_dept)

if wasSectionDraft:
    signingMovement = first movement where
        action_type='signed_and_forwarded' AND from_dept == originating_dept
    row1.sender_user_desg = signingMovement?.actor OR currentHolder
    row1.signature_path  = signingMovement?.secretary_signature_path
    row1.receiver        = signingMovement?.toUserDesg OR draftTargetDepartment.title
else:
    row1.sender_user_desg = originatingUserDesg
    row1.signature_path  = firstSent.secretary_signature_path
    row1.receiver        = firstSent.toUserDesg

push row1 = {
    summary.body,
    sender, designation, dept,
    receiver, signature_path
}

for each subsequent movement:
    skip if remarks IS NULL
    skip if action_type NOT IN (sent_to_department, signed_and_forwarded, remarks_added)
    skip if action_type='sent_to_department' AND from_dept == to_dept (internal routing)
    skip if movement == signingMovement (already row 1)

    if action_type == 'remarks_added':
        sender = movement.toUserDesg     // show the secretary, not the DEO
        receiver = "" (none)
        is_draft = (signature_path IS NULL)
    else:
        sender = movement.actor
        receiver = movement.toUserDesg
        is_draft = false

    push row
```

##### Row rendering
For each row:
- If `is_draft` → show **yellow "Draft — Pending Secretary Signature"** tag above content + amber left border on the content cell
- Show movement number, date, content (HTML), signature image (if any), sender name + designation + department, sending date, receiver (only for non-remarks_added)
- Horizontal divider between rows

#### C. Right Sidebar (~3 cols, sticky)

##### C.1 Attachments card
- **Main Summary PDF**: shown first with "View" button (opens PDF in popup/iframe)
- **Flag attachments** (rest): each shows file-type icon + flag name (extracted from `[Flag: X]` prefix) + View/Download button
- **Draft attachments highlighted in yellow** (when `showDraftActions` is true and the attachment was added in the current cycle)
- **Remove (×) button** appears only on attachments where:
  - User is `isCurrentSecretaryHolder` OR `isDraftReturnedToMe`
  - AND attachment was uploaded by the current user OR user is the secretary
  - AND attachment.created_at >= last arrival time of summary in this dept (or no arrival = same dept always)
  - AND it's not the main PDF

##### C.2 Movement Timeline card
- For each `signed_and_forwarded` and `sent_to_department` movement (excluding same-dept returns), show:
  - From dept → To dept
  - Action label, date, actor name
- Plus a "Current Pending" item with status badge, current dept, current holder

##### C.3 Action card (only shown to specific users)
Three mutually exclusive blocks based on `$isDraftReturnedToMe`, `$isCurrentSecretaryHolder`, and `$showDraftActions`:

**Block 1 — `isDraftReturnedToMe` (DEO with returned draft/remarks):**
- Red header "Returned for Amendments"
- Yellow box showing secretary's instructions + timestamp
- If `originating_user_desg_id == me AND summary_type == section_draft`:
  - Button: **"Edit & Resubmit Draft"** → `GET /summaries/{id}/edit-draft`
- Else (returned remarks user):
  - Button: **"Edit & Resubmit Remarks"** → `GET /summaries/{id}/edit-remarks`

**Block 2 — `isCurrentSecretaryHolder AND showDraftActions` (Secretary with draft-able remarks):**
- Orange info box explaining
- Button: **"Edit Drafted Remarks"** → opens edit modal (POST `update-draft-content`)
- Button: **"Sign & Forward"** → opens forward modal (POST `forward`)
- Button: **"Return to Section"** → opens return modal (POST `return-to-section`)
- Button: **"Share Internally"** → opens share modal (POST `share-internally`)

**Block 3 — `isCurrentSecretaryHolder AND !showDraftActions` (Secretary with regular external summary):**
- Button: **"Add Remarks & Forward"** → forward modal (with required remarks textarea)
- Button: **"Share Internally"** → share modal
- Button: **"Print Remarks on Summary"** (only if `canPrintRemarks` is true)

##### C.4 Local Correspondence card
Always rendered when `localLinks` is non-empty (filtered to user's own department only).
- Each daak/file shows icon + title + truncated subject + View button
- Daak: blue background; File: green background

##### C.5 Internal Forwards card
Only when `current_status IN (SHARED_INTERNALLY, COLLECTING_REMARKS, READY_TO_FORWARD)`.
- For each `visibleInternalForward`: forwardedTo name, designation, "Assigned by", status pill (Pending / Remarks Submitted / Closed)

#### D. Internal Correspondence card (below sheet)
**Visible only to current secretary OR draft-returned user OR users with local links visible.**

A unified, time-sorted timeline of:
- Internal forwards (`visibleInternalForwards`) — color-coded by status (yellow=pending, green=submitted, grey=closed). Shows forwardedBy → forwardedTo with badges, instruction, response remarks (forwarding remark + paras), "Use In Forward" buttons (only for the secretary).
- Returned-to-section movements **filtered to my dept only** (`from_dept == to_dept == myDept`). Red border, "Returned" badge, secretary's name, return remarks.

#### E. Internal Files card
Inside the `isCurrentSecretaryHolder` block. Lists internal e-files attached to internal forwards, with View buttons that open a styled file preview modal.

#### F. Your Action Required card
Only shown when `$myInternalForward != null` (user has a pending internal forward to act on).
- Shows the secretary's instruction
- Two tabs:
  - **Draft Remarks & Return**: link to `/summaries/{id}/internal-action/{forwardId}` (full-page form) + "Create Internal E-File" link
  - **Forward to Another User**: dropdown of dept users, instruction textarea, "Forward to Selected User" button → POST `forward-internally`
- **Previous Internal Correspondence card** (above the action card) — shows submitted remarks from this user's chain so they have context.

