## 15. Edge Cases & Gotchas

- **A user can be in only one department at a time** for a given user_desg. Mobile login should fetch the active user_desg and resolve `currentDepartmentId` from it.
- **A summary can be in the same dept twice** (forwarded out, then the next dept returns it via signed_and_forwarded). The "arrival cutoff" logic handles this — the most recent arrival is what defines "current cycle".
- **Resubmit Remarks does not create a new movement** — it updates the existing unsigned `remarks_added` so the timestamps reflect the latest version.
- **The DEO never sees a "Sign" button** because the `isSecretaryOrActing` check fails for role 2.
- **Acting Secretary detection is by designation title string match**, so be careful with translations or case differences when reading the field on mobile.
- **The "Submitted Internal Remarks" card is now called "Internal Correspondence"** and shows a unified timeline of forwards + returns.
- **Local links are filtered per-viewer-department** (a user in dept B does not see dept A's linked daak/files even if they can view the summary).
- **The yellow "Draft" tag on the document** indicates an unsigned `remarks_added` row that the secretary still needs to sign.

