## 17. Recommended API Wrapper (for the backend team)

The mobile app should call a JSON API rather than the HTML routes. Recommend creating an `/api/v1/summaries/...` mirror of each route that:
1. Returns JSON resources (e.g. `SummaryResource`, `SummaryDetailResource`)
2. Authenticates via Sanctum/Passport tokens
3. Returns the **computed view state flags** alongside the data so the mobile app doesn't have to recompute every time
4. Returns enums as integer codes (status, action_type) and English labels (for display)
5. Pre-resolves URLs (signed `?-expiring URLs for attachments`)
6. Returns paginated cursor-based lists for the inbox/tabs

